e_desc";s:68:"WebAsyst Update Server is generating an installation package for you";s:21:"upd_m_status_download";s:11:"Downloading";s:25:"upd_m_status_downoad_desc";s:26:"Downloading... %s of %s MB";s:19:"upd_m_status_unpack";s:20:"Preparing to install";s:24:"upd_m_status_unpack_desc";s:41:"Unpacking archive with the latest version";s:27:"upd_m_status_before_install";s:24:"Install prepare complete";s:17:"upd_m_upd_details";s:24:"View this update details";s:18:"upd_m_upd_db_count";s:34:"Number of databases to be updated:";s:17:"upd_m_btn_install";s:7:"Install";s:20:"upd_m_status_install";s:17:"Installing update";s:25:"upd_m_status_install_desc";s:73:"Installation is in progress...<br>Please wait and don't close the window.";s:26:"upd_m_status_install_compl";s:35:"Installation completed successfully";s:31:"upd_m_status_install_compl_desc";s:16:"Installation log";s:24:"upd_m_err_state_download";s:53:"An error occured while downloading the latest version";s:24:"upd_m_btn_retry_download";s:9:"Try again";s:22:"upd_m_err_state_unpack";s:65:"An error occured while unpacking archive with the lastest version";s:23:"upd_m_err_state_install";s:36:"An error occured during installation";s:23:"upd_m_btn_retry_install";s:9:"Reinstall";s:32:"upd_m_btn_retry_download_install";s:29:"Retry download & installation";s:13:"upd_m_inf_upd";s:6:"Update";s:32:"upd_m_inf_description_howitworks";s:17:"How update works?";s:21:"upd_m_inf_description";s:1751:"<ol><li>WebAsyst Installer sends a request for update to <strong>my.webasyst.net</strong> update server. This request includes license number you entered on "General settings" Installer screen.</li><li>If your license number is approved, update server creates an archive with your purchased applications.</li><li>WebAsyst Installer automatically downloads this archive and runs installation — overwrites existing files with the updated files from the archive, and then implements all necessary meta data update instructions.</li></ol> <p style="font-size: 100%;">Your WebAsyst data is not affected in any way (all your data is stored in separate folders data/ and published/publicdata/, and these folders are never affected during update).<br><br>The process is automated — WebAsyst Installer handles all steps of the update. You don't need to download software update manually and upload updated files by FTP. Manual installation may be required only if your web server configuration does not allow to run update for some reason. In such circumstances WebAsyst Installer will notify you about the error, and you will have to contact your server administator to tune server settings and make update possible.<br><br>If you used built-in design editors to alter WebAsyst frontend design (e.g. storefront design in "Shopping cart" application), your changes will not be lost during update (files that you altered are stored in published/publicdata/ folder which is not "envolved" in the update). However, if you used third-party tools for editing files (e.g. text editor or other programs for editing HTML) your changes may be lost during the update. Safety of your frontend design will be assured only in case you use built-in design editing tools.";s:14:"upd_m_inf_list";s:7:"See the";s:18:"upd_m_inf_upd_link";s:20:"full list of changes";s:18:"upd_m_inf_upd_inst";s:77:"to be installed with this update.<br> Following applications will be updated:";s:19:"upd_m_inf_meta_link";s:8:"metadata";s:19:"upd_m_inf_meta_inst";s:15:"will be updated";s:18:"upd_m_inf_upd_desc";s:11:"What's new?";s:19:"upd_m_inf_meta_desc";s:34:"View meta data update instructions";s:12:"upd_m_notice";s:209:" <strong style="color: red">IMPORTANT:</strong> <strong>Update is not recommended if you customized your WebAsyst PHP source code or database structure</strong> since your changes may be lost after the update.";s:21:"upd_m_erase_agreement";s:181:" I agree that this update will replace all my WebAsyst source code files with files from the newest version, which means that all changes that I made to the source code may be lost.";s:23:"upd_m_license_agreement";s:103:"I agree that my license number and my WebAsyst installation URL will be sent to WebAsyst update server.";s:22:"upd_m_changelog_oneapp";s:16:"Application "%s"";s:23:"upd_m_changelog_allapps";s:16:"All applications";s:23:"upd_m_changelog_version";s:20:"Versions %d&mdash;%d";s:13:"install_title";s:28:"WebAsyst Installation Wizard";s:19:"install_step1_title";s:19:"Adding MySQL server";s:17:"install_step_info";s:4:"Step";s:16:"install_continue";s:17:"Continue &gt;&gt;";s:19:"install_step2_title";s:17:"Creating Database";s:18:"install_step2_desc";s:380:"At this step you are offered to create your first WebAsyst database. Later you will be able to create as many databases as you need using WebAsyst Administrator tools. As a database you can either use new or existing MySQL database. If you want to use existing database, we strongly recommend using empty database which does not contain previously created tables or other objects.";s:20:"install_step2_finish";s:29:"Setup Successfully Completed.";s:16:"install_link_wba";s:28:"Access to WebAsyst Installer";s:15:"install_link_db";s:17:"Login to WebAsyst";s:18:"install_work_dbkey";s:17:"Your database key";s:18:"install_link_login";s:11:"To login as";s:22:"install_link_login_use";s:3:"use";s:21:"install_finish_notice";s:59:"We recommend you to print this page for further references.";s:9:"wbs_title";s:18:"WebAsyst Installer";s:13:"wbs_installer";s:9:"Installer";s:21:"install_maillog_title";s:43:"WebAsyst Installation Wizard Notification

