Login name                  :";s:25:"migarate_note_description";s:980:"<p>This tool will transfer all data from your Shop-Script FREE, PRO or PREMIUM online store to WebAsyst including products, orders, customers, general and checkout settings, information pages and more &mdash; everything except your storefront design and source code modifications.<br><br> We can not integrate your customized Shop-Script design into WebAsyst automatically because of differences in design template structures.<br><br> You will have to introduce changes to WebAsyst storefront design by yourself. We included several storefront themes with WebAsyst &mdash; feel free to use any of them.<br><br> <b>Important:</b> this tool can transfer data only from Shop-Script database <i>that were not modified</i>. If you changed your Shop-Script database structure manually, this tool may work incorrectly.<br><br> During transfer data will be <strong>copied</strong> to WebAsyst, and your Shop-Script based online store will continue to work without any changes.<br><br></p>";s:22:"migarate_target_header";s:33:"Select your new WebAsyst database";s:21:"migarate_target_dbkey";s:24:"Copy Shop-Script data to";s:24:"migarate_target_language";s:33:"Your default Shop-Script language";s:22:"migarate_source_header";s:20:"Shop-Script database";s:20:"migarate_source_same";s:66:"Shop-Script and new WebAsyst Shop-Script are in the same database.";s:25:"migarate_source_same_desc";s:224:"Choose this option if you installed WebAsyst to the same database as Shop-Script installed. Only database content will be copied from your Shop-Script installation (product pictures and files will not be copied) to WebAsyst.";s:26:"migarate_source_ss_version";s:19:"Shop-Script version";s:20:"migarate_source_auto";s:46:"Enter path to Shop-Script folder (recommended)";s:25:"migarate_source_auto_desc";s:268:"Just enter path to directory where your older Shop-Script version is installed, and Installer will automatically read database connection settings and transfer Shop-Script content to your new WebAsyst Shop-Script including database content, product pictures and files.";s:27:"migarate_source_auto_wapath";s:34:"Path to your WebAsyst installation";s:27:"migarate_source_auto_sspath";s:32:"Path to Shop-Script installation";s:30:"migarate_source_auto_path_desc";s:87:"Enter absolute path to your Shop-Script folder (in the same manner as path to WebAsyst)";s:26:"migarate_source_auto_files";s:31:"Copy product pictures and files";s:22:"migarate_source_custom";s:43:"Enter database connection settings manually";s:27:"migarate_source_custom_desc";s:239:"Provide full database connection settings to your Shop-Script database (host, port, user, password and database name). Only database content will be copied from your Shop-Script installation (product pictures and files will not be copied).";s:18:"migarate_agreement";s:101:"I agree that this will <i>erase all data currently stored my new WebAsyst Shop-Script application</i>";s:12:"migrate_nosc";s:302:"WebAsyst Shop-Script is not installed. Complete WebAsyst Shop-Script application installation prior to transferring data from your older Shop-Script version. To complete WebAsyst installation make sure you have Shop-Script in the installed application list and that your storefront is working properly.";s:16:"migrate_complete";s:37:"Data transfer performed successfully!";s:14:"migrate_header";s:30:"Shop-Script FREE, PRO, PREMIUM";s:22:"migrate_button_migrate";s:13:"Transfer data";s:24:"migrate_agreement_header";s:45:"WebAsyst Shop-Script information to be erased";s:22:"migrate_agreement_text";s:286:"This operation will empty your new WebAsyst shopping cart database prior to transferring data from your older Shop-Script version. If you have several WebAsyst applications installed, this upgrade routine will only erase shopping cart products and leave content of other services as is.";s:22:"migrate_charset_custom";s:51:" Reinterpret Shop-Script database encoding to UT